metadata.name: Acequia #296
metadata.description:
Acequia (‚Äúah-seh-kee-uh‚Äù) - a Spanish adaptation of the Arabic word as-sƒÅqiya, meaning ‚Äúwater carrier‚Äù. 

In our second collaboration, Rich and Rick are back with our blend of generative code, intricate design, attention to detail, and a splash of charm. 

‚Ä®Acequias are traditional irrigation canals used to distribute rainwater and snowmelt along a complex network of narrow channels. They are found in Spain, the American Southwest, and northern Mexico, where they are essential for sustaining fields, orchards, and gardens in semi-arid regions. ‚Ä®‚Ä®
Our aim in this series is to capture the essence of these waterways in bold geometric designs. Each piece is inspired by a mountain village or town in Andalusia (southern Spain). 

The location determines the cube designs and construction rules that are used to build the final output. These are combined with striking day/night palettes, outline styles, scales, climates, and a few surprises of course!


Controls (in live view): 

- Press [p] to pause water animation 
- Press [e] to complete water animation 
- Press [r] to reset water animation 
- Press [s] to save the current image 
- Press [h] for a high-res output suitable for printing 
- Press [b] to toggle the border

metadata.name: Geode #39
metadata.description:
A single seed shape is chosen from 13, and placed onto the plane. At every step, a copy of this seed is laid edge-to-edge adjacent to an existing shape, without causing any overlaps. This copy is colored based on the edge it shares with the existing shape. The process continues until the animation completes.

New shapes are placed closest to a moving target. In some mints, this target is slow moving, causing new shapes to expand radially from the seed. In other mints, this target races around, causing new shapes to chase it. 

Each of the 13 shapes forms different patterns under different circumstances. Not all patterns will be explored.

Controls:
  - SPACE: Pause/unpause the animation.
  - ENTER: Skip the animation.
  - R: Restart the animation.

URL Params:
  - "preview=1": Skip the animation.
  - "flex=1": Adapt the boundaries to the size of the window.
  - ‚Äúslow=1‚Äù: Draw only one shape per frame.

metadata.name: Harmonies #9
metadata.description:
Harmonies is a color palette generator created for fxhash anniversary. The generator chooses from 7 possible color harmonies "Complementary, Split-Complementary, Analogous, Triadic, Tetradic, Square, Analogous and Monochromatic" to create harmonic color palettes. When i studied colors back in time, i used to take a color or a couple of colors and paint strokes on paper with watercolors to understand and learn how they stand out together. This piece is a result of those studies.

5 stroke compositions for 'Split-Complementary, Analogous and Triadic'
3 stroke compositions for 'Tetradic, Square and Monochromatic'
3 stroke compositions for 'Complementary'
2 color mods "Saturated and Muted' and 6 rendering methods for strokes 'Random Saturated, Random Brightness, Random Brightness & Saturation, Saturation Gradient, Brightness Gradient, Brightness & Saturation Gradient'

Save image by pressing 's'
Save colors as hex array ready to be used by pressing 'p'

Created with p5.js | Murat Atimtay 2022

metadata.name: sewn gate #63
metadata.description:
Now what?
Warmth and comfort?

The lines create carpet patterns with different patterns and angles each time. Squares, rhombuses, plain embroidery and many others.
Why carpets?

They are very attractive with their comfort. A house or apartment with carpets always seems more residential and warm, no matter what kind of carpet. One color or pattern doesn't matter. It performs not only a design or warming function, but also a pleasant one for the soul. I hope I was able to make your day comfortable!

metadata.name: Swedish Forest #292
metadata.description:
If I had to choose a place where time was frozen and where I could contemplate the landscape for eternity this place would be a scandinavian forest.
I have been contemplating these kind of landscape for a very long time both in Sweden and in the Pyrenees where the ecosystem is very similar.
This project generates an illustration of a scandinavian forest in many different situations. At day and at night, in every season of the year, next to a lake or not, with steep hills or at the plains, snowing, with preponderance of some plant species over others, etc.
The artwork is also drawn in various paint modes and layouts.

The sun or the moon may be visible, the moon shows always the actual moon phase based on the current date.
The reflection on the lake is the fxhash morse endcoded.


Developed in vanilla js using svg and canvas
Rendering can be unresponsive on slow devices
Click or touch to switch to Parallax mode, just move the mouse or finger.


[S] Download in SVG format
[D] Download in PNG format

Features:

Layout: Landscape, Portrait, Square
PredominantSpecies: Blueberry, Lingonberry, Calluna, Rocks, None
Trees: Mixed, PinesAndFirs, Birches, None
Season: Spring, Summer, Fall, Winter
DayNight: Day, Night
PaintStyle: Normal, Stroke, Paint, WhiteOnBlack, BlackOnWhite
ColorStyle: Normal, Crazy
HasLake: True, False
HasTrees: None, Few, Many, Crowded

metadata.name: fx(haish) / the Generator #163
metadata.description:
fx(haish) is my contribution to #fxhashturnsone
fx(haish) is not a finished product
fx(haish) is a co-creation experiment
fx(haish) is a fun exploration of a mixed GenAI process

fx(haish) is my Happy Birthday to fx(hash). 

Have fun, collectors!


// HOW TO PARTICIPATE

Step 1. Mint or collect ‚Äúfx(haish) - the Generator‚Äù
Step 2. Visit https://www.arqtistic.com/fx(haish) to generate your ‚Äúfx(haish) - The AI City‚Äù based on your mint. You have 20 tries.
Step 3. Await further instructions.


// FURTHER INFO

This algorithm has been designed to produce images which are suitable for the subsequent AI generation. The token consists of a random number of randomly placed and sized rectangles, filled with a noise gradient pattern. In short, Diffusion AI Models thrive on noise.

The AI generation uses Stable Diffusion 1.5 through an API designed by the 330ai team (@Pixelmindai). The WebUI has been developed by Nik0gda (@AntonCebanu2). AI Prompt has been designed (by me) to produce images of Cities, but you can possibly make it do other things, if you try hard enough.

metadata.name: INTERFERENCES #264
metadata.description:
INTERFERENCES is an abstract representation of the incredible collaboration between artists, collectors and developers on fxhash.

Each edition is composed of a multitude of lines representing each individual on the platform. The color of each line defines the role of each individual in this universe. Through their interactions, and the interferences they produce, each line participates in the creation of a common work.

Happy birthday fxhash! And congratulations to all those who work for its success.

Primary sales are donated to the Processing Foundation

[KEYBOARD]

* Press [0] to save 3 individual SVG for each color set of lines + the background image PNG

metadata.name: BINARY WORDS #232
metadata.description:
I drew my first 8x8 pixel binary image on 11/08/2022 with 'iloveyou' encoded for my wife, it was our 10-year anniversary on this day.  After that made this generative stuff for fxhash's birthday bash.

#fxhashturnsone

Donations:
25% to ThreeJs team

The image contains a binary coded word or phrase with a length of 8 characters. The grays represents 0, the other colors represents 1. One row -> one character. Should be proceed decoding from left to right and from top to bottom.

An example: 'iloveyou'

01101001
01101100
01101111
01110110
01100101
01111001
01101111
01110101

The fxrandom selects a word and the program converts it to binary data. After that, the background (ground and sky) is randomly generated from color schemes. Then the binary gray colors are drawn. Also the color of light next to null colors is randomly generated from color schemes. Random affects also the animation.

The animation stops when you do these interactions below, then restarts after a few seconds of inactivity.

Press spacebar to change:

- frame view -> without frame
- without frame -> original 8x8px size
- original 8x8px size -> frame view

Press 's' to save an svg from current view.

Notes:
- Build with ReactJs and TweenJs
- Every upcoming day, half of the remaining pieces are burned.

Happy Birthday fxhash community!
I'm glad to be among you!

metadata.name: a pale reflection #181
metadata.description:
a canvas is prepared; grids and vignette applied.

marks are added (or not)

a drawing method is chosen

the drawing method is iterated, resulting in a heavily stippled image

the image is sent to a shader

various maths occur inside the shader

the resulting shaded image is then given a border

and thus to the screen

a pale reflection - original music here: https://rtsixty.bandcamp.com/track/pale-reflection 
listen while waiting to be signed.

99.9% of royalties to original minter.

metadata.name: 365 Tentacles #143
metadata.description:
Wow, Fxhash ! What a year !

For #fxhashturnsone I decided to explore how far I could take a simple concept: drawing 365 tentacles.
This turned out to be an interesting exercise, as having a strict limitation seemed to spark more ideas than when having complete freedom. There's a lot you can do with 365 things !

99.9% of primary sales go to the Processing Foundation.

Key commands:
's' to save a png image
'1', '2', '4' to change resolution
'+', '-' to change rendering zoom
